<module>
    <h>Calum</h>
    <p><g>Calum</g>
        <en>Malcolm</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/anthroponymic_proper_nouns">anthroponymic
            proper noun</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>Calum</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>Calum</m> – nominative/dative (singular)</li>
                <li><m>Chaluim</m> – genitive (singular)</li>
                <li><m>A Chaluim!</m> – vocative</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p>Examples with <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Calum</m> mór.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is big.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Calum</m> ag obair.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>In a conjoined subject with <a href="?gd=agus"><g>agus</g></a>
                <en>and</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Màiri agus Calum</m> trang an diugh – tha iad ag obair anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today – they are working in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
